We recommended that Management require the:
a) Inventory Committee to submit the RPCI of all inventory accounts in prescribed format and with the complete information;
b) Municipal Accountant and Supply Officer to reconcile the RPCI and other property records with the books of accounts and make necessary adjustments or corrections for a fair presentation of the accounts in the Financial Statement;
c) The Supply Officer or Municipal Treasurer to prepare and maintain stock cards for each inventory item; and
d) The Municipal Health Office to create and maintain inventory system for monitoring the date expiration of drugs and medicines to prevent spoilage/wastage.

We recommended that Management require the:
a) Municipal Accountant and Supply Officer to reconcile the RPCPPE with the books of accounts and make necessary adjustments or corrections for a fair presentation of the accounts in the Financial Statement;
b) Inventory Committee to conduct complete physical count and submit the lacking RPCPPE;
c) Municipal Accountant to submit the SB Resolution on the land exchange; to look for the SB Resolution; and
d) Supply Officer or Municipal Treasurer to maintain property cards for each type of asset; and
e) Human Resource Management Officer II to initiate increase in the manpower requirement of the General Service Office for subsequent hiring of administrative assistants to facilitate preparation of reports and maintenance of property cards.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive require the BAC and/or the Municipal Engineer to:
a) Submit the missing attachments/supporting documents;
b) Adopt the prescribed format of Approved Contract in DPWH D.O. 197 series 2016; the Approved Budget for the Contract;
c) Prepare and include PERT/CPM as part of the contract submitted to the Audit Team; d) Include copy of the Bidding documents as attachment to the contract; e) Require attachment of photocopy of Official Receipt for payment of bidding documents when bidder/s submit their Bidding documents and to issue bidding notification letter to all bidders who submitted their proposal; f) Invite COA representative, private group representative and NGO representative at least five calendar days before the date of Post-qualification; g) Mark/stamp the month, date and year when the bidder submit other supporting documents as required in the 2016 Revised IRR of RA 9184; h) Provide a written explanation why the bidders who did not comply with labor laws were not disqualified and still awarded the three contracts; and i) Ensure that bidders adhere to labor laws and regulations to avoid abuse of contractors for paying workers below the required minimum wage rate. We further recommended that the Accountant ensure completeness of supporting documents prior to processing of claims.

We recommended that the Municipal Accountant to submit the lacking documents to the Audit Team for verification and henceforth, ensure that all documentary requirements for emergency purchase under RA No. 11469 are complied with before processing claims. We further recommended that Management require the:
a) Municipal Accountant to submit the required documents such as RISs, Delivery Receipt/Charge Invoice, Inspection and Acceptance Report, Driver’s Trip Tickets and RIS/RIVs; 
b) Inspectorate team to fill-up properly the IAR as to Date Number, date of inspection and acceptance; 
c) Drivers/passengers requesting fuel/gasoline to prepare and properly fill up driver’s trip tickets; and 
d) General Services Office to facilitate repair of the defective speedometers to provide control in the use of the vehicles and consumption of fuel and oil.

